fx:CLUSTER.ho:DESC: This is an example CAN cluster. The CAN cluster defines what baudrate is used for all nodes on the network.
This is an example of a FlexRay Cluster. It has been configured using the "Easy" edit mode. You can still view the details by selecting the "Expert" edit mode and clicking on "Edit...".
This cluster can be used with the NI CAN Demo Box: http://sine.ni.com/nips/cds/view/p/lang/en/nid/201709

fx:SIGNAL.ho:DESC: Sets the mode for both CAN and DAQ bargraphs. Values: 0 - Dot mode 1 - Bar mode
Values: 0 - Disable all 1 - Waveform0-Sawtooth0-Switches only 2 - Waveform1-Sawtooth1 only 3 - Enable all
Values: 0 to 9 - 0.1Hz to 1Hz in 0.1Hz increments 9 to 18 - 1Hz to 10Hz in 1Hz increments 18 to 117 - 10Hz to 1000Hz in 10Hz increments
Values: 0 - CAN baud rate 1 - CAN transmit status 2 - CAN/DAQ 3 - Function generator output 4 - Function generator frequency 5 - LCD contrast
Periodic rate of WAVEFORM0_SAW0_SWITCHES_FROM_CDB equals delay multiplier * 200 nanoseconds. Values: Range is 0 to 65535.
